== Two or three flights? ==
On the third of two dives, the outer portion of the starboard wing folded up and the ailerons became locked.
Third of two? Is it third of three, second of two, or is this some Britishism I've never before encountered? <small class="autosigned">— Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[Special:Contributions/96.245.118.188|96.245.118.188]] ([[User talk:96.245.118.188|talk]]) 07:22, 6 December 2014 (UTC)</small><!-- Template:Unsigned IP --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->
